            "title": "Mutual Fund and ETF Fees Remained Near Historic Lows in 2025",
            "id": "40bf666d-a425-40fc-ae76-dd26a6873540",
            "description": "On March 25, 2026, in Washington, a recent report from the Investment Company Institute revealed a notable decrease in average expense ratios for actively managed and index mutual funds over the past 29 years. This trend has led to an overall decline in mutual fund expense ratios, indicating a positive shift in the investment landscape. The report highlights the significance of this development in the financial sector, showcasing the impact of reduced expenses on investments. This data signifies a beneficial change for investors, with numbers reflecting a consistent downward trajectory in mutual fund expense ratios over nearly three decades.",
